        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "IP65 protects against low-pressure water jets from any direction (6.3mm nozzle, 12.5 liters/min). IP66 protects against high-pressure water jets from any direction (12.5mm nozzle, 100 liters/min). IP69K protects against close-range high-pressure, high-temperature water jets (80°C / 176°F at 80-100 bar / 1160-1450 PSI). IP69K is required for food plants using CIP, foam-and-rinse, or high-pressure steam sanitation."
