        Sanitary & Washdown Conveyors
      </h1>
      <div class="text-xl text-ink-muted leading-relaxed max-w-3xl space-y-4">
        <p>
          Sanitary conveyors are food-processing conveyor systems designed for thorough cleaning through washdown, CIP (Clean-in-Place), or COP (Clean-out-of-Place) methods. They use IP65 through IP69K rated components, stainless steel frames with crevice-free welds, self-draining surfaces, and FDA-compliant contact materials to meet USDA acceptance and 3-A Sanitary Standards.
        </p>
        <p>
          Washdown conveyors protect food products from cross-contamination by allowing sanitation crews to clean equipment in place using water, chemicals, foam, and high-pressure rinses without damaging motors, bearings, or electrical components.
        </p>
