      <h2 id="selection-heading" class="font-display text-4xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide mb-8">
        How to Specify a Sanitary Conveyor
      </h2>
      <div class="text-lg text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-4">
        <p>
          Specifying a sanitary conveyor correctly requires answering these questions before contacting manufacturers. Missing any one of these leads to respecification, change orders, or (worst case) a conveyor that fails audit.
        </p>
        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 ml-2">
          <li><strong class="text-ink">What is the product?</strong> Raw or cooked? Direct contact or sealed package? Temperature at the conveyor (frozen, ambient, hot)?</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">What is the cleaning protocol?</strong> Wipe-down, hose-down, high-pressure washdown, CIP, or COP? Frequency (every shift, daily, weekly)?</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">What cleaning chemicals are used?</strong> Quaternary ammonium, chlorinated alkaline, peracetic acid, caustic, or other? This determines 304 vs. 316 stainless and belt material compatibility.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Which regulatory standard applies?</strong> USDA, 3-A, BISSC, or general FDA/FSMA compliance?</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">What is the environment?</strong> Ambient dry, humid, wet floor, outdoor, or temperature-controlled?</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">What throughput is required?</strong> Products per minute, line speed (FPM), and <a href="/conveyor-types/accumulation-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">accumulation requirements</a>.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">What upstream/downstream equipment connects?</strong> <a href="/conveyor-types/transfer-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Transfer points</a>, elevation changes, and <a href="/conveyor-functions/collating-laning/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">laning/collating</a> requirements.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>
          Collect these answers into your RFQ document before requesting quotes. This ensures you receive comparable quotes from multiple manufacturers and prevents scope creep during the project.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
